catching the whole thing
on tape.

33
00:01:20,967 --> 00:01:24,061
That way, nobody can deny
the existence of extraterrestrials

34
00:01:24,158 --> 00:01:25,540
or the fact
that they're in this town,

35
00:01:25,547 --> 00:01:26,422
because all the proof
they need

36
00:01:26,428 --> 00:01:27,920
is gonna be right here
on the screen.

37
00:01:34,475 --> 00:01:35,163
Hello?

38
00:01:35,485 --> 00:01:37,353
Dave, you get
everything boarded up?

39
00:01:37,366 --> 00:01:39,921
<i>Yeah. If the roof holds, I think
everything should be okay.</i>

40
00:01:40,185 --> 00:01:41,182
<i>You get everyone out of town?</i>

41
00:01:41,285 --> 00:01:42,931
Yeah, the family's
headed north.

42
00:01:43,028 --> 00:01:44,122
We're on our way back
down to the sound

43
00:01:44,127 --> 00:01:45,822
to see if we can round up
Szura's hybrids.

44
00:01:46,367 --> 00:01:47,991
Round 'em up?
Round 'em up how?

45
00:01:48,156 --> 00:01:48,851
<i>I don't know.</i>

46
00:01:49,926 --> 00:01:51,523
But if they're primed
for some kind of insurrection-

47
00:01:51,528 --> 00:01:52,621
then we'll kill 'em.

48
00:01:53,608 --> 00:01:54,532
You hear that?

49
00:01:54,768 --> 00:01:57,062
Yeah. Sounds like
a great plan.

50
00:01:57,187 --> 00:01:59,301
Listen, stay close to the phone.
We may need your help.

51
00:01:59,658 --> 00:02:02,340
Okay. Hey, Russ,
be careful, all right?

52
00:02:02,507 --> 00:02:03,143
<i>You, too.</i>

53
00:02:03,855 --> 00:02:04,480
Thanks.

54
00:02:09,426 --> 00:02:12,173
- How many were out there?
- At least a hundred.

55
00:02:12,547 --> 00:02:13,270
Maybe more.

56
00:02:15,626 --> 00:02:16,520
And they were just...

57
00:02:17,645 --> 00:02:20,183
- sitting underwater?
- Standing underwater.

58
00:02:20,695 --> 00:02:21,801
Like an army.

59
00:02:29,065 --> 00:02:31,952
<i>since initial reports had the storm landing
in west palm beach...</i>

60
00:02:31,965 --> 00:02:33,201
Not my initial report.

61
00:02:34,385 --> 00:02:37,122
<i>So many people in a panic, and many of them
at this hour still trying to find...</i>

62
00:02:38,387 --> 00:02:39,691
You did everything
you could, Larkin.

63
00:02:39,695 --> 00:02:41,471
You told everyone
it was coming to Homestead.

64
00:02:42,087 --> 00:02:42,831
Yeah.

65
00:02:42,837 --> 00:02:44,651
How much longer
to the motel, mom?

66
00:02:45,346 --> 00:02:47,272
I'm guessing
at least another hour.

67
00:02:48,298 --> 00:02:50,043
Shouldn't we be
on the main road by now?

68
00:02:51,236 --> 00:02:52,932
I think
this is the main road.

69
00:02:53,967 --> 00:02:57,072
- None of the phones are working.
- The towers must be down.

70
00:02:57,267 --> 00:02:59,173
I wanna call Lewis.
I wanna see how he's doing.

71
00:02:59,395 --> 00:03:00,560
I'm sure he's fine,
honey.

72
00:03:01,307 --> 00:03:04,121
The hospital's probably
the safest place he could be right now.

73
00:03:04,236 --> 00:03:05,151
Yeah, I'd be
much more worried

74
00:03:05,155 --> 00:03:06,841
about dad and Tom
than I would Lewis.

75
00:03:07,067 --> 00:03:09,901
Lewis will be fine. He's not
gonna hunt down the aliens.

76
00:03:13,166 --> 00:03:14,281
Mariel, look out!

77
00:03:17,775 --> 00:03:18,521
Oh, my god...

78
00:03:19,025 --> 00:03:19,821
You okay?

79
00:03:19,908 --> 00:03:20,682
Is everybody okay?

80
00:03:20,837 --> 00:03:21,862
- Mommy?
- Are you okay?

81
00:03:21,906 --> 00:03:23,601
- I'm okay.
- Yeah, I think so.

82
00:03:24,156 --> 00:03:25,240
Rose, you okay?

83
00:03:25,685 --> 00:03:26,370
Uh, yeah.

84
00:03:26,386 --> 00:03:27,192
We're all right.

85
00:03:31,976 --> 00:03:35,850
- Maybe we can move it.
- Well, you're not gonna move it.

86
00:03:37,267 --> 00:03:39,292
Um, Kira, Jesse?

87
00:03:39,815 --> 00:03:41,651
Let's see what
we can do with this.

88
00:03:53,737 --> 00:03:54,672
Lewis.

89
00:04:00,235 --> 00:04:01,310
Oh... hey, guys.

90
00:04:01,785 --> 00:04:02,483
What's up?

91
00:04:03,048 --> 00:04:03,953
How you feeling?

92
00:04:04,826 --> 00:04:05,610
All right.

93
00:04:06,127 --> 00:04:07,822
Little concerned
about the storm, I guess.

94
00:04:11,495 --> 00:04:12,271
What's wrong?

95
00:04:12,628 --> 00:04:14,343
You have any idea
where the sheriff is tonight?

96
00:04:14,808 --> 00:04:17,211
Yeah, he took his family
out of town.

97
00:04:17,496 --> 00:04:18,303
He's back.

98
00:04:19,195 --> 00:04:20,561
Sanchez called and said

99
00:04:20,567 --> 00:04:23,471
he came through the blockade
on highway 1 about an hour ago.

100
00:04:23,906 --> 00:04:25,301
Did you try him
on the radio?

101
00:04:25,335 --> 00:04:27,300
We think he killed
deputy Munger, Lewis.

102
00:04:31,428 --> 00:04:34,633
We found Munger's body handcuffed
in the passenger seat of his own car.

103
00:04:35,277 --> 00:04:37,303
Someone drove it off
into a flatbed.

104
00:04:37,635 --> 00:04:39,123
He was decapitated.

105
00:04:40,448 --> 00:04:41,432
My god.

106
00:04:41,846 --> 00:04:43,571
Underlay was the last person
with him.

107
00:04:45,197 --> 00:04:48,833
But the sheriff could never
have done something like that.

108
00:04:49,126 --> 00:04:49,930
I mean, he couldn't!

109
00:04:49,936 --> 00:04:52,302
We think Munger was killed
because he was different, Lewis.

110
00:04:53,456 --> 00:04:54,382
Different like you.

111
00:04:55,477 --> 00:04:57,161
And like me and Troy here.

112
00:04:57,176 --> 00:04:58,612
The sheriff
is different, too.

113
00:04:58,648 --> 00:05:00,141
Yeah, but he seems
to have forgotten that his job

114
00:05:00,155 --> 00:05:01,520
is to protect his people.

115
00:05:03,906 --> 00:05:05,511
We think he may have
fallen in with some folks

116
00:05:05,515 --> 00:05:07,251
who don't
want us around anymore...

117
00:05:10,457 --> 00:05:13,671
maybe some of the same folks
who put you in this hospital.

118
00:05:17,668 --> 00:05:18,592
I don't believe you.

119
00:05:19,038 --> 00:05:22,593
The sheriff has always wanted everybody
to live and work together!

120
00:05:22,705 --> 00:05:23,520
Then where is he?

121
00:05:24,326 --> 00:05:26,711
On a night like this, when his people
and his town need him the most-

122
00:05:26,717 --> 00:05:27,603
Where is he?

123
00:05:31,716 --> 00:05:33,560
His time has passed, Lewis.

124
00:05:34,096 --> 00:05:35,291
It's time for us now.

125
00:05:37,585 --> 00:05:42,230
And it's time for you to decide
which side you're on.

126
00:05:45,186 --> 00:05:46,540
Will you help us find him?

127
00:05:47,087 --> 00:05:49,910
I- I don't-I really
have no idea where he is.

128
00:05:50,338 --> 00:05:52,230
Well, then maybe you know
someone who does.

129
00:06:10,017 --> 00:06:11,743
Stupid freaking door.

130
00:06:15,797 --> 00:06:16,772
First aid kit.

131
00:06:17,266 --> 00:06:18,793
Come on, first aid kit.

132
00:06:19,215 --> 00:06:20,473
I'm bleeding to death here.

133
00:06:40,065 --> 00:06:42,053
- Is this the place?
- Yeah.

134
00:06:44,717 --> 00:06:45,503
Who's that?

135
00:06:46,385 --> 00:06:48,270
Vargas-the guy I was
telling you about.

136
00:06:48,588 --> 00:06:50,513
He was here earlier.
I think he's working for Szura.

137
00:06:51,877 --> 00:06:52,713
What's he doing?

138
00:06:53,165 --> 00:06:54,671
Standing guard,
I imagine.

139
00:06:56,006 --> 00:06:57,060
Stupid bastard.

140
00:06:57,066 --> 00:06:58,141
Let's go.

141
00:07:10,586 --> 00:07:12,191
Looks like someone else
has been here, too.

142
00:07:19,436 --> 00:07:20,161
Hey.

143
00:07:21,265 --> 00:07:22,423
Hey, Vargas...

144
00:07:28,800 --> 00:07:29,912
Was he a friend of yours?

145
00:07:31,590 --> 00:07:32,283
No.

146
00:07:36,113 --> 00:07:38,175
So this is where you saw
all these people in the water?

147
00:07:38,175 --> 00:07:39,021
Right here?

148
00:07:39,155 --> 00:07:41,410
Yeah, but I can't
see anything now.

149
00:07:42,026 --> 00:07:43,533
I can't tell
if they're still in there.

150
00:07:45,818 --> 00:07:49,252
They're not.
They're gone.

151
00:07:51,596 --> 00:07:52,413
They're gone.

152
00:07:55,247 --> 00:07:56,373
Russ.

153
00:08:08,908 --> 00:08:10,033
It's their clothes.

154
00:08:11,108 --> 00:08:12,843
Why would they leave
all their clothes?

155
00:08:14,868 --> 00:08:16,213
Let's go back
in the truck.

156
00:08:24,578 --> 00:08:26,951
Why would these people be
running around without clothes?

157
00:08:29,398 --> 00:08:31,681
I'm afraid they may have
changed into uniforms.

158
00:08:31,855 --> 00:08:34,991
- Uniforms?
- Military uniforms.

159
00:08:39,398 --> 00:08:42,813
Szura was supposed to be
training these people to reenter society.

160
00:08:43,426 --> 00:08:44,223
As soldiers?

161
00:08:46,668 --> 00:08:48,680
The reasoning was that
during the next hurricane,

162
00:08:48,976 --> 00:08:52,620
if some of the national guard
were actually hybrids themselves,

163
00:08:52,816 --> 00:08:57,730
that it might make the transition easier
for the new people.

164
00:08:59,776 --> 00:09:01,160
Well, you didn't...

165
00:09:01,468 --> 00:09:02,813
arm them, did you?

166
00:09:06,016 --> 00:09:08,032
Oh, no.

167
00:09:12,436 --> 00:09:14,212
I trusted the man,
Russell.

168
00:09:15,966 --> 00:09:17,461
And in the beginning, he...

169
00:09:18,387 --> 00:09:20,403
he didn't give me
any reason not to.

170
00:09:20,415 --> 00:09:23,630
Is there anything else that
you'd like to share with me?

171
00:09:27,046 --> 00:09:28,781
Tt's no use, mom.
It's not gonna move.

172
00:09:29,118 --> 00:09:30,751
We just have to
all do it together.

173
00:09:31,087 --> 00:09:32,623
We've tried. It's not working!

174
00:09:37,036 --> 00:09:38,372
Hey!
Hey!

175
00:09:38,378 --> 00:09:40,043
Hey!

176
00:09:45,487 --> 00:09:46,412
Larkin!

177
00:09:46,615 --> 00:09:49,013
- You folks all right?
- We got stuck.

178
00:09:49,048 --> 00:09:50,613
I don't think we're
gonna get out tonight.

179
00:09:50,625 --> 00:09:51,643
Can you give us a lift?

180
00:09:51,987 --> 00:09:53,211
Pretty crowded back there,

181
00:09:53,276 --> 00:09:54,950
but I think
we can make some room.

182
00:09:55,055 --> 00:09:55,723
Great.

183
00:09:56,186 --> 00:09:57,373
You guys get on the truck.

184
00:09:57,685 --> 00:09:58,972
Come on. They're gonna
give us a ride.

185
00:09:58,977 --> 00:10:00,923
- What about Carlita?
- We'll take her.

186
00:10:03,337 --> 00:10:04,203
Come on.

187
00:10:04,417 --> 00:10:05,361
Come, honey.

188
00:10:11,976 --> 00:10:14,131
Come on, Rose.
Come on. It's okay.

189
00:10:17,786 --> 00:10:19,140
Watch your step.

190
00:10:21,365 --> 00:10:22,550
You better hurry, ma'am.

191
00:10:38,076 --> 00:10:41,091
Mr. Szura,
we've got another load coming.

192
00:11:09,816 --> 00:11:13,001
- Hey!
- Mr. Groves, I'm Lewis Sirk.

193
00:11:13,687 --> 00:11:15,631
- I'm sheriff underlay's deputy-
- deputy, yeah.

194
00:11:15,635 --> 00:11:16,601
Yeah, I know.

195
00:11:16,675 --> 00:11:18,240
Come in, come in.

196
00:11:18,867 --> 00:11:20,810
Come in, come in. I thought
you were in the hospital.

197
00:11:20,827 --> 00:11:22,481
Yeah, I, uh,
got better.

198
00:11:22,738 --> 00:11:24,920
This is deputy Buell
and deputy Armis.

199
00:11:25,005 --> 00:11:26,831
I'd shake your hand,
but I'm bleeding here.

200
00:11:27,405 --> 00:11:28,272
Mr. Groves...

201
00:11:28,468 --> 00:11:29,163
Dave.

202
00:11:29,906 --> 00:11:33,021
Dave, do you happen to know
where the sheriff is tonight?

203
00:11:33,968 --> 00:11:35,140
Yeah, uh...

204
00:11:36,757 --> 00:11:39,272
he and, uh, Russell
took everyone up to, um...

205
00:11:44,278 --> 00:11:46,193
uh... why?

206
00:11:46,197 --> 00:11:47,270
Why do you ask?

207
00:11:47,487 --> 00:11:50,240
Some of our emergency management
folks need to talk to him.

208
00:11:51,106 --> 00:11:52,340
Don't you guys
have radios?

209
00:11:53,065 --> 00:11:53,952
He's out of range.

210
00:11:54,937 --> 00:11:56,953
Well,
I'll tell you what.

211
00:11:57,868 --> 00:11:59,591
If I hear from him,
I'll let you know, okay?

212
00:12:00,535 --> 00:12:03,113
When do you expect
to be hearing from him?

213
00:12:04,156 --> 00:12:05,293
I don't know, really.

214
00:12:06,176 --> 00:12:07,442
Maybe I won't. I don't know.

215
00:12:07,917 --> 00:12:09,231
You say he's with
your brother-in-law?

216
00:12:09,395 --> 00:12:10,100
Yeah.

217
00:12:11,226 --> 00:12:12,313
Yeah,
they went together.

218
00:12:12,636 --> 00:12:13,551
What are they doing?

219
00:12:14,707 --> 00:12:16,770
You know, I don't know what
this is about.

220
00:12:16,795 --> 00:12:17,961
What are we talking about?

221
00:12:23,966 --> 00:12:25,193
How'd you hurt your hand?

222
00:12:26,978 --> 00:12:27,740
I cut it.

223
00:12:28,247 --> 00:12:30,180
Uh, I cut it on a door.

224
00:12:31,395 --> 00:12:32,750
You mind if I take a look?

225
00:12:35,526 --> 00:12:37,380
I used to work
in an emergency room.

226
00:12:42,075 --> 00:12:43,850
Oh, boy,
that doesn't look good.

227
00:12:46,406 --> 00:12:47,553
Where is he?
Where is underlay?

228
00:12:47,566 --> 00:12:49,331
- Troy! Troy!
- Stop! Stop! Please!

229
00:12:49,545 --> 00:12:50,253
I don't know!

230
00:12:52,898 --> 00:12:54,843
Damn it, man, what the hell
is wrong with you?!

231
00:12:55,338 --> 00:12:57,201
Troy, I think mr. Groves
is telling the truth.

232
00:12:57,365 --> 00:12:58,233
Oh, you think so?

233
00:12:58,237 --> 00:12:59,462
You think I'm telling the truth?

234
00:12:59,815 --> 00:13:00,751
So I think...

235
00:13:02,257 --> 00:13:04,801
that we're all gonna
just wait right here

236
00:13:04,806 --> 00:13:07,463
until the sheriff
or this brother-in-law

237
00:13:07,625 --> 00:13:09,322
decides to make contact.

238
00:13:10,788 --> 00:13:12,823
Does that work for you,
mr. Groves?

239
00:13:36,735 --> 00:13:38,232
I don't think we're going
in the right direction.

240
00:13:39,838 --> 00:13:41,692
I think we're headed back
towards homestead.

241
00:13:46,008 --> 00:13:47,721
How far is it
to the shelter?

242
00:13:48,785 --> 00:13:49,970
Not sure on that, ma'am.

243
00:13:51,735 --> 00:13:53,061
Well, can I at least
borrow your radio?

244
00:13:53,065 --> 00:13:54,990
Call my husband,
tell him we're all okay?

245
00:13:57,815 --> 00:13:59,653
This only operates
on a special frequency.

246
00:14:00,485 --> 00:14:01,710
Won't be of any use to you.

247
00:14:05,278 --> 00:14:06,293
What's wrong with him?

248
00:14:09,908 --> 00:14:11,151
He's a hybrid.

249
00:14:12,067 --> 00:14:13,743
And he knows I'm one, too.

250
00:14:18,975 --> 00:14:20,540
Our best bet is to call
all the different agencies-

251
00:14:20,545 --> 00:14:21,880
police, fire,
emergency management-

252
00:14:21,885 --> 00:14:23,603
let them know
what we're really facing.

253
00:14:24,126 --> 00:14:25,083
Won't make a difference tonight.

254
00:14:25,088 --> 00:14:26,503
Everyone thought
the storm was going north,

255
00:14:26,506 --> 00:14:27,742
and that's where they are.

